Merkel’s Party, Opposition SPD Drop in German Poll, Bild Says

-- B y   A n d r e a s   C r e m e r
-- 
2011-02-13T09:26:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-13/merkel-s-party-opposition-spd-drop-in-german-poll-bild-says.html
Support for German Chancellor  Angela Merkel ’s Christian Democratic Union and the opposition Social
Democratic Party fell in a weekly poll, Bild am Sonntag said.  Merkel’s party declined 1 percentage point to 34 percent,
while the Social Democrats lost 2 points to score 25 percent,
 Bild am Sonntag  reported, citing its weekly in-house survey.  The pro-business Free Democrats, junior partner in Merkel’s
ruling national coalition government, gained 1 point to 6
percent, while the Left Party held steady at 10 percent. Backing
for the  Green Party  increased 2 points to 19 percent.  German voters will cast ballots in seven of the country’s
16 federal states this year. Hamburg, Germany’s second largest
city, starts the electoral marathon on Feb. 20.  The newspaper provided no margin of error for the poll and
didn’t specify when the survey was conducted and the number of
respondents it included.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andreas Cremer at 
 acremer@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:  Kenneth Wong  at 
 kwong11@bloomberg.net . 